OL,3,CHomegrown doctors could help the
OL,4,Cchronic shortage of rural GPs
OL,6,F"I was previously a pharmacist in a
OL,7,Fvillage, and I love that community
OL,8,Ffeel. And knowing your patients,
OL,9,Fknowing their stories, supporting them
OL,10,Fthrough their life challenges. So
OL,11,Fthat's what really ticks for me."
OL,13,FLocal GP Dr Sara Proudfoot is one of
OL,14,Fthe trainers for the students. She
OL,15,Fsaid that they would also get the
OL,16,Fopportunity to 'embed' in one of 17
OL,17,Fsurgeries in Dumfries and Galloway to
OL,18,Fget more hands-on experience.
